---
import Base from '@layouts/Base.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '@components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Accessibility | Cumberland Septic Hub"
  description="Cumberland Septic Hub's accessibility commitment — WCAG-conscious design, keyboard navigation, form accessibility and how to report barriers."
>
  <div class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <Breadcrumbs crumbs={[{ label: 'Home', href: '/' }, { label: 'Accessibility' }]} />
      <h1>Accessibility Statement</h1>
      <p>Septic problems don't discriminate; neither should the website for solving them.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <div class="container prose" style="max-width:52rem;">
      <h2>Our commitment</h2>
      <p>
        Cumberland Septic Hub aims to be usable by everyone, including people using screen
        readers, keyboard navigation, magnification and other assistive technology. The website is
        built with Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.1 AA–conscious practices.
      </p>

      <h2>What the website does</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Semantic HTML with one main heading per page and a logical heading order</li>
        <li>A skip-to-content link and consistent keyboard navigation with visible focus states</li>
        <li>Accessible navigation dropdowns and FAQ accordions</li>
        <li>Form fields with real labels — never placeholder-only — and error messages linked to their fields</li>
        <li>Status messages announced to screen readers during form submission</li>
        <li>Strong color contrast and large touch targets</li>
        <li>Reduced-motion support respecting the <code>prefers-reduced-motion</code> setting</li>
        <li>Descriptive link and button text and image alt text</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Known limitations</h2>
      <p>
        Third-party components — such as the Cloudflare Turnstile verification widget — are
        provided by their vendors, and their accessibility is partly outside this website’s
        control.
      </p>

      <h2>Report a barrier</h2>
      <p>
        If any part of this website is difficult to use with assistive technology, please say so
        through the <a href="/contact/">contact page</a> — reports are genuinely welcome and
        inform fixes. If a form is unusable for you, requests can also be made by phone; the
        number appears in the site header on every page.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Base>
